HEADWORD: Personalty
<hw>Per"son*al*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being a person; personality.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Personal property, as distinguished
from realty or real property.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Personate</ent>⟦br⟧
